<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - PRIMING THE
        LUBRICATING SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PRIMING THE LUBRICATING SYSTEM</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install new lube oil filters.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pressure prime the lubrication system with oil, prior to starting as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using oil leak detector
                        <emph type="bold">SE-1632</emph>, attach the line from the oil leak detector to the oil cooler
                        at the oil drain pipe plug. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150663">6.63</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Inject sufficient oil into the engine to fill the oil filters and charge the entire
                        system.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>If oil enters the engine at other than the cooler, oil will be blocked by the oil
                                filter and will not flow to the lube oil pump.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <specpara>
                        <warning>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                                rotate any diesel engine when priming with oil to prevent engine from accidentally
                                starting.
                            </para>
                        </warning>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">After priming, check the oil level before the engine is put back into service. Refer
                        to chart for proper oil capacity.
                    </para>
